3 Days Ago “After collecting N20,000, they then shaved our hair without our consents.” Despite condemnations by Nigerians, Hisbah group has continued its push for an Islamic agenda in the North. The agency established to enforce Sharia law in some states in the region recently banned stylish haircuts, sagging of trousers, playing of music at social events by disk jockeys and tricycle riders from adorning their vehicles with pictures considered to be obscene and against the tenets of Islam. This was in addition to other unusual directives reeled out by the Islamic police. Hisbah recently made headlines for shaving stylish haircuts of young men in Kano and arresting people for improper dressing. A barber and his customers were recently arrested in the state for allegedly giving haircuts said to be offence to Islam to the affected customers. They are also notorious for destroying truckloads of alcoholic drinks.